values.content:
=Write a sales email for this venue:

Venue: {{ $json.business_name }}
Type: {{ $json.category }}
City: {{ $json.city }}
Reviews: {{ $json.review_count }}
Rating: {{ $json.rating }}
Pain Signals: {{ $json.pain_signals }}
Decision Maker Role: {{ $json.decision_maker_role }}
Estimated Monthly Loss: ${{ $json.estimated_monthly_loss }}
Score: {{ $json.score }}

Tailor the pitch to their specific situation. If they have pain signals, reference them. If high volume, emphasize revenue opportunity. If they have tech already, emphasize consolidation.

parameters.jsCode:
const leadData = $node["Get Qualified Leads"].json;

let emailData;
try {
  const content = $json.message.content;
  emailData = JSON.parse(content);
} catch (e) {
  console.error('Failed to parse email JSON:', e);
  // Fallback email
  emailData = {
    subject: `Quick question about ${leadData.business_name}`,
    opener: `Hi, I noticed ${leadData.business_name} serves high volumes.`,
    body: `Most hospitality venues lose 25-40% of potential orders because guests avoid lines over 8 minutes. Seamlessly fixes this with mobile QR ordering integrated directly into your existing POS. We recently helped a similar ${leadData.category} increase revenue 30%. Would a 15-minute demo make sense?`,
    ps: ''
  };
}

// Construct full email body
const fullBody = `${emailData.opener}\n\n${emailData.body}${emailData.ps ? '\n\nP.S. ' + emailData.ps : ''}`;

// Add signature
const signature = `\n\nBest,\n[Your Name]\nFounder, Seamlessly\n[Your Phone]\n[Your Website]`;

return {
  ...leadData,
  email_subject: emailData.subject,
  email_body: fullBody + signature,
  status: leadData.score >= 15 ? 'Ready to Send - Hot' : 'Ready to Send - Qualified',
  last_activity: new Date().toISOString()
};

parameters.message:
